-- India’s NTPC Tamilnadu Energy Seeks 500,000 Tons of Steam Coal
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2012-12-06T09:51:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-06/india-s-ntpc-tamilnadu-energy-seeks-500-000-tons-of-steam-coal.html
NTPC Tamilnadu Energy Co ., an Indian
power producer, is seeking to import 500,000 metric tons of
steam coal for its unit in southern  India .  The company, a joint venture of  NTPC Ltd. (NTPC) , India’s biggest
power producer, and Tamilnadu Generation and Distribution Corp.,
wants the fuel delivered at its 1,500 megawatt Vallur power
plant, said S. Sukumaran, a senior manager, by telephone from
Chennai.  The last date for submitting bids is Dec. 17, he said
without giving more details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
